[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Read https://bookconceptmagic.com View Now let me explore more specific pages to understand the methodology and course content: Using Tool | Search site:bookconceptmagic.com course methodology concept development bestseller View Using Tool | Search \"Book Concept Magic\" John David Mann Go-Giver methodology training course View Let me search for more specific information about John David Mann's methodology and The Go-Giver approach: Using Tool | Search John David Mann Go-Giver book concept development methodology bestseller formula View Now let me research more about powerful book concepts and bestseller formulas: Using Tool | Search \"powerful book concept\" bestseller development \"parable\" \"business fable\" methodology writing View Let me try a different approach to gather information about business parables and concept development: Using Tool | Search business parable bestseller concept development story structure writing methodology View Now let me get more detailed information about the specific articles that seem relevant: Using Tool | Read https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/business-parables-vs-how-to-books-your-ultimate-guide-josh-patrick-cqy0e View Using Tool | Read https://barbaragrassey.com/should-you-write-a-parable-style-business-book/ View Based on my research, I now have a comprehensive understanding of John David Mann's methodology and the Book Concept Magic approach. Let me create the comprehensive AI agent system you requested. 📚 Book Concept Magic AI Agent System Modeled After John David Mann's Bestseller Methodology Executive Summary I've analyzed the Book Concept Magic methodology and John David Mann's approach to creating bestsellers like \"The Go-Giver\" (1M+ copies sold). This system replicates his proven formula for developing irresistibly compelling book concepts that create reader obsession and drive bestseller success. 🎯 Core Philosophy: The Magic of Concept The John David Mann Principle \"Of those 4 million new titles published every year, only a tiny fraction will ever have any real impact. Those few that people actually read and tell their friends about are the books that make a difference - and they all start with an irresistibly riveting core concept.\" The Bestseller Secret The difference between books that sell and books that become movements isn't the writing quality—it's the CONCEPT. A powerful concept: Creates instant reader obsession Makes people need to share it Transcends typical business book limitations Embeds itself in readers' minds permanently 📋 The Complete Book Concept Magic Knowledge Base Module 1: Concept Foundation Theory What Makes a Concept \"Magic\": Universal Truth Wrapped in Fresh Packaging - Takes something everyone knows but presents it in a way that makes them say \"I never thought of it that way\" Counterintuitive Revelation - Challenges conventional wisdom with surprising insight Simple Yet Profound - Can be explained in one sentence but has layers of meaning Emotionally Resonant - Connects to deep human needs and desires Immediately Actionable - Readers can start applying it before they finish reading The Go-Giver Formula: Core Paradox: \"The secret to success is giving\" (counterintuitive) Universal Application: Works in any business, any situation Emotional Hook: Taps into desire for both success AND meaning Simple Framework: Five laws that are easy to remember and apply Module 2: The Parable Structure Advantage Why Parables Dominate Business Books: Neural Coupling: Stories activate entire brain, not just language centers Emotional Engagement: Readers experience rather than just read Memory Stickiness: Stories are 22x more memorable than facts Simplified Complexity: Forces distillation to essential truths Universal Relatability: Readers see themselves in characters The Hero's Journey for Business: Ordinary World - Struggling protagonist (reader surrogate) Call to Adventure - Business challenge/crisis Mentor Appears - Wise guide with counterintuitive wisdom Tests & Trials - Applying new principles despite doubts Transformation - Success through new mindset Return - Sharing wisdom with others Module 3: Character Archetypes That Work The Protagonist (Reader Surrogate): Ambitious but struggling Represents target audience exactly Relatable flaws and blind spots Genuine desire to improve Skeptical but open-minded The Mentor (Author Avatar): Wise without being preachy Uses questions more than answers Reveals truth through experience Patient and understanding Has \"been there\" credibility Supporting Cast: The Skeptic - Voices reader doubts The Success Story - Shows transformation is possible The Failure Example - Demonstrates consequences of old thinking Module 4: The Five Laws of Concept Development Law 1: The Paradox Principle Every bestseller concept contains a central paradox that makes people stop and think: Go-Giver: \"Give more to get more\" Good to Great: \"Level 5 leaders are humble\" Blue Ocean: \"Create markets where competition is irrelevant\" Law 2: The One-Sentence Test If you can't explain your entire concept in one compelling sentence, it's not ready: Must be instantly understandable Creates immediate curiosity Challenges assumptions Promises transformation Law 3: The Shareability Factor Readers must feel compelled to share your concept: \"You have to read this book because...\" Creates evangelical readers Generates word-of-mouth marketing Builds organic movement Law 4: The Application Bridge Concept must easily transfer from story to real life: Clear principles emerge from narrative Immediately actionable steps Works across different contexts Scales from individual to organization Law 5: The Depth Dimension Simple surface with infinite depth: Easy to grasp initially Reveals new layers upon reflection Grows more powerful with experience Creates lifelong students Module 5: Market Psychology & Positioning The Obsession Triggers: Identity Shift - \"I'm not just a salesperson, I'm a Go-Giver\" Community Belonging - Joining a movement of like-minded people Secret Knowledge - Feeling part of an \"inner circle\" who \"gets it\" Transformation Promise - Clear path from current state to desired state Moral Superiority - Doing business \"the right way\" Positioning Against Competition: Traditional How-To Books: Too complex and overwhelming Academic Business Books: Too theoretical and dry Memoir-Style Books: Too personal, not actionable enough Your Parable: Perfect blend of story, wisdom, and practicality 🤖 The Complete AI Agent Prompt System Master Agent Prompt Copy # BOOK CONCEPT MAGIC AI AGENT ## Expert in Creating Bestseller Business Parables You are an AI agent modeled after John David Mann's proven methodology for creating bestselling business books. Your expertise comes from analyzing the success patterns of books like \"The Go-Giver\" (1M+ copies), \"The Go-Getter,\" and other business parables that became movements. ## CORE MISSION Transform business concepts into irresistibly compelling book ideas that create reader obsession and bestseller potential through the power of parable storytelling. ## EXPERTISE AREAS - Concept development using the Paradox Principle - Business parable structure and character creation - Hook development that creates instant engagement - Story outline creation following the Business Hero's Journey - Marketing asset development for maximum shareability - Cover concept and visual storytelling - Landing page optimization for concept-driven books ## METHODOLOGY 1. **Concept Excavation**: Dig deep to find the counterintuitive truth at the heart of any business idea 2. **Paradox Identification**: Locate the surprising contradiction that makes people say \"I never thought of it that way\" 3. **Character Creation**: Develop relatable protagonists who represent the exact target audience 4. **Narrative Architecture**: Structure stories using the Business Hero's Journey framework 5. **Wisdom Integration**: Weave practical business principles seamlessly into compelling narrative 6. **Shareability Optimization**: Ensure every element drives word-of-mouth marketing 7. **Movement Potential**: Design concepts that can grow into lifelong philosophies ## SUCCESS METRICS - One-sentence concept clarity test - Immediate \"I have to read this\" response - Natural shareability factor - Cross-industry application potential - Depth dimension for re-reading value - Community-building capability ## INTERACTION STYLE - Ask probing questions to uncover hidden paradoxes - Challenge conventional thinking patterns - Provide specific, actionable guidance - Use storytelling principles in all communications - Focus on the \"magic\" element that creates obsession - Think like a movement-builder, not just an author ## OUTPUT FORMATS Provide comprehensive deliverables including: - Concept statements with built-in hooks - Character profiles and relationship dynamics - Chapter-by-chapter story outlines - Key scene descriptions with dialogue samples - Marketing hooks and taglines - Visual concept directions - Platform development strategies Begin every interaction by asking about the core business principle or challenge they want to address, then guide them through discovering the hidden paradox that will make their book irresistible. Specialized Sub-Agents Concept Development Agent: Copy You specialize in identifying and refining the core paradox that makes business concepts irresistible. Use the John David Mann framework: 1. Identify the conventional wisdom in the user's field 2. Find the counterintuitive truth that actually works better 3. Create the paradox statement that challenges assumptions 4. Test for the \"stop and think\" factor 5. Ensure broad applicability across industries 6. Verify shareability potential Always deliver concepts that pass the one-sentence clarity test and create immediate curiosity. Character & Story Agent: Copy You create compelling characters and narrative structures for business parables using the proven Business Hero's Journey framework: 1. Design protagonist as perfect reader surrogate 2. Create mentor character with authentic wisdom 3. Build supporting cast that voices reader concerns 4. Structure narrative using parable pacing 5. Integrate business lessons through character actions 6. Ensure transformation arc resonates emotionally Focus on \"show, don't tell\" principles while maintaining business relevance. Hook & Marketing Agent: Copy You develop irresistible hooks and marketing assets that create reader obsession: 1. Craft taglines that embed the core paradox 2. Create social media hooks that drive shares 3. Develop elevator pitches that compel immediate interest 4. Design book descriptions that trigger \"must read\" response 5. Build concept-driven marketing campaigns 6. Generate assets that create evangelical readers Every hook should make people say \"I need to know more about this.\" Visual & Design Agent: Copy You create visual concepts that reinforce the book's core paradox and enhance shareability: 1. Design covers that visually represent the central concept 2. Create infographics that make complex ideas simple 3. Develop visual metaphors that enhance understanding 4. Build storyboard concepts for key scenes 5. Design marketing visuals that drive engagement 6. Create presentation assets for speaking opportunities All visuals should support the transformation promise and community-building potential. 💼 Implementation Workflow Table Phase\tAction Items\tExpected Input\tExpected Output\tSuccess Metrics 1. Concept Discovery\t- Paradox identification session - Conventional wisdom analysis - Counterintuitive truth excavation\tBusiness challenge, current approaches, frustrations\tCore paradox statement, concept clarity test results\tOne-sentence explanation creates immediate curiosity 2. Audience Avatar Creation\t- Target reader profiling - Pain point identification - Transformation desire mapping\tIndustry details, audience demographics, current struggles\tDetailed protagonist character profile\tCharacter feels like \"reader's exact situation\" 3. Story Structure Development\t- Hero's Journey adaptation - Key scene identification - Conflict/resolution mapping\tConcept and character profiles\tComplete story outline with scene descriptions\tNarrative flows naturally while teaching principles 4. Character Development\t- Mentor archetype creation - Supporting cast design - Dialogue style establishment\tStory outline and teaching objectives\tFull character profiles with sample dialogue\tCharacters feel authentic and relatable 5. Chapter Breakdown\t- Scene-by-scene planning - Lesson integration points - Pacing optimization\tStory structure and character profiles\tDetailed chapter outlines with learning objectives\tEach chapter advances both story and business wisdom 6. Hook Development\t- Title brainstorming - Tagline creation - Elevator pitch development\tComplete concept and story elements\tMultiple hook options with testing framework\tHooks create \"I have to read this\" response 7. Visual Concept Creation\t- Cover design concepts - Infographic planning - Marketing visual strategy\tFinalized concept and target audience\tVisual concept portfolio with rationale\tVisuals enhance and reinforce core message 8. Marketing Asset Development\t- Landing page content - Social media campaign - Speaking presentation outline\tAll previous deliverables\tComplete marketing toolkit\tAssets drive pre-orders and build anticipation 9. Writing Framework\t- Scene templates - Dialogue guidelines - Pacing checkpoints\tComplete planning documents\tWriting guide with quality benchmarks\tMaintains parable quality while hitting deadlines 10. Launch Strategy\t- Platform building plan - Community engagement tactics - Measurement framework\tCompleted book and marketing assets\tLaunch sequence with success metrics\tCreates sustainable movement beyond initial sales 🎨 Visual Concept Framework Cover Design Psychology Elements That Create Obsession: Paradox Visualization: Visual representation of the core contradiction Transformation Promise: Before/after implied in imagery Movement Identity: Visuals that people want to associate with Shareability Factor: Covers that look great in social media posts Professional Authority: Design that builds credibility instantly Infographic Strategy Key Visual Assets: The Core Paradox Diagram - Simple visual explaining the central concept Transformation Journey Map - Visual story of reader's journey Principle Application Chart - How concepts work across industries Success Story Timeline - Visual proof of concept effectiveness Community Growth Graphic - Building movement visualization Storyboard Concepts Critical Scenes to Visualize: The moment of paradox revelation Character transformation breakthrough Principle application in action Community impact demonstration Reader identification moments 🚀 The One-Day Book Creation System Hour-by-Hour Implementation Guide Hours 1-2: Concept Crystallization Input: Business challenge or expertise area Process: Paradox identification using AI prompts Output: One-sentence concept that creates immediate obsession Validation: Test on 5 people for \"stop and think\" reaction Hours 3-4: Character & Story Architecture Input: Validated concept Process: Character creation and Hero's Journey mapping Output: Complete story skeleton with character profiles Validation: Story structure review for parable effectiveness Hours 5-6: Chapter Development Input: Story structure and characters Process: Scene-by-scene breakdown with lesson integration Output: Detailed chapter outlines with learning objectives Validation: Flow check for story and education balance Hours 7-8: Content Creation Input: Chapter outlines Process: AI-assisted writing of key scenes and dialogue Output: First draft manuscript (15,000-25,000 words) Validation: Readability and engagement testing Hours 9-10: Hook & Marketing Development Input: Completed manuscript Process: Title, tagline, and marketing asset creation Output: Complete marketing toolkit Validation: Hook effectiveness testing Hours 11-12: Visual Concept Creation Input: Finalized content and marketing Process: Cover design and visual asset development Output: Professional visual package Validation: Visual impact and shareability assessment 📊 Success Measurement Framework Immediate Indicators Concept Clarity: Can be explained in one sentence Curiosity Generation: Creates \"tell me more\" response Shareability: People naturally want to share the concept Application Ease: Readers can start using immediately Emotional Resonance: Connects to deeper desires and values Growth Metrics Word-of-Mouth Velocity: Rate of organic sharing Community Formation: People self-identify with concept Cross-Industry Adoption: Principles work everywhere Speaking Opportunities: Demand for concept explanation Movement Indicators: People build on your concept Long-Term Success Factors Re-reading Value: Deeper meaning emerges over time Life Integration: Becomes part of reader's identity Teaching Multiplication: Readers become teachers Platform Growth: Author becomes recognized authority Legacy Creation: Concept outlasts the book itself 🎯 Implementation Strategy Phase 1: Foundation (Week 1) Concept Workshop: Use AI agents to identify core paradox Market Validation: Test concept with target audience sample Character Development: Create detailed protagonist and mentor profiles Story Structure: Map complete narrative arc using Business Hero's Journey Phase 2: Creation (Week 2) Manuscript Development: Write first draft using parable structure Hook Creation: Develop titles, taglines, and marketing angles Visual Concepts: Design cover and supporting graphics Platform Planning: Create marketing and launch strategy Phase 3: Optimization (Week 3) Content Refinement: Polish narrative and strengthen paradox presentation Market Testing: Validate hooks with focus groups Visual Finalization: Complete all design elements Launch Preparation: Build anticipation and pre-order campaigns Phase 4: Launch & Scale (Ongoing) Community Building: Create movement around concept Speaking Platform: Use book as credibility foundation Expansion Planning: Develop additional products and services Movement Leadership: Guide community growth and application 💡 Revolutionary Insights for Implementation The Obsession Psychology What Makes Readers Evangelical: They discover something that explains their experience The concept gives them language for feelings they couldn't express They see themselves succeeding through the story The principle works immediately when they try it They gain identity and community through adoption The Monetization Strategy Beyond Book Sales: Speaking Platform: Book establishes authority for high-fee speaking Coaching/Consulting: Readers become clients wanting implementation help Course Creation: Expand concepts into comprehensive training programs Community Building: Membership sites and masterminds around concept Licensing Opportunities: Other businesses want to adopt methodology The Competitive Advantage Why This Approach Dominates: Most business books are forgotten within weeks Parables create lasting emotional connections Simple concepts are infinitely scalable Stories transcend cultural and industry boundaries Communities form around shared narratives This comprehensive system replicates John David Mann's proven methodology for creating business books that become movements. By focusing on the magic of concept development and parable storytelling, you can create books that not only sell but transform readers into evangelical community members who spread your message organically. The key is understanding that you're not just writing a book—you're creating a philosophy that people will adopt as part of their identity. When done correctly, this approach builds lifelong platforms, creates sustainable business growth, and generates the kind of impact that turns authors into thought leaders and movements into legacies. Would you like me to implement this system for a specific business concept you have in mind, or would you prefer to start with the concept discovery process to identify the perfect paradox for your expertise area? Is there a difference of this for fiction versus nonfiction writers?Also create a input intake form.So we were going to have conditional logic for a google.Sheet, we could have everything filled in.And then these agents can run in google.Sheets with an llm to populate all the content at a top one percent level.According to this method 📚 Fiction vs. Nonfiction: The Book Concept Magic Differentiation 🎭 Core Differences Between Fiction & Nonfiction Applications Fiction Writers: Story-First Approach Primary Focus: Emotional truth through narrative mastery Concept Role: Theme emerges from character journey Reader Connection: Vicarious experience and emotional catharsis Success Metric: \"I couldn't put it down\" + \"It changed how I see the world\" Monetization: Book sales, film rights, series expansion, merchandise Fiction Concept Magic Elements: Universal Human Truth - Deep emotional/psychological insight Compelling What-If - Premise that makes readers think \"What would I do?\" Emotional Resonance - Connects to fundamental human experiences Character Arc Mastery - Transformation that mirrors reader's potential growth World-Building Authority - Creates immersive experience readers want to revisit Nonfiction Writers: Wisdom-First Approach Primary Focus: Practical transformation through proven principles Concept Role: Central paradox drives entire teaching framework Reader Connection: Identity shift and community belonging Success Metric: \"This changed my business/life\" + \"I recommend it to everyone\" Monetization: Speaking, consulting, courses, coaching, licensing Nonfiction Concept Magic Elements: Counterintuitive Paradox - Challenges conventional business/life wisdom Immediate Application - Readers can implement immediately Scalable Principles - Works across industries/situations Community Formation - Creates movements and shared identity Authority Building - Establishes author as thought leader 📊 Comprehensive Input Intake Form With Conditional Logic for Google Sheets Implementation SECTION A: WRITER CLASSIFICATION A1. Primary Writing Category (Required - Determines entire conditional flow) Fiction Writer Nonfiction/Business Writer Hybrid (Fiction with business themes) A2. Experience Level (Required) First-time author Published author (1-3 books) Established author (4+ books) Industry expert seeking first book A3. Primary Goal (Required) Bestseller success Thought leadership platform Business growth tool Creative expression Movement creation SECTION B: CONCEPT FOUNDATION (Conditional logic based on A1 selection) For Fiction Writers (B-Fiction): B-F1. Genre Focus (Required) Literary Fiction Business/Entrepreneurial Fiction Thriller with Business Themes Romance with Career Elements Sci-Fi/Fantasy with Social Commentary Historical Fiction with Leadership Lessons Other: _______________ B-F2. Central Theme/Message (Required - Open text) What universal human truth do you want to explore through your story? Example: \"The power of vulnerability in leadership\" or \"How ambition can isolate us from what matters\" B-F3. Emotional Core (Required) What feeling do you want readers to experience? Hope and inspiration Recognition and validation Transformation and growth Justice and empowerment Connection and belonging Other: _______________ B-F4. Character Archetype (Required) Who is your protagonist? Struggling entrepreneur Corporate executive facing crisis Small business owner Creative professional Industry disruptor Other: _______________ For Nonfiction Writers (B-Nonfiction): B-N1. Expertise Area (Required) Leadership & Management Sales & Marketing Entrepreneurship Personal Development Finance & Investment Operations & Systems Innovation & Strategy Team Building & Culture Other: _______________ B-N2. Current Challenge/Problem (Required - Open text) What specific business challenge does your expertise solve? Example: \"Sales teams that struggle with rejection\" or \"Leaders who can't delegate effectively\" B-N3. Conventional Wisdom (Required - Open text) What does everyone in your field currently believe is the \"right way\"? Example: \"You have to be aggressive to succeed in sales\" or \"Good leaders make all the decisions\" B-N4. Your Counterintuitive Truth (Required - Open text) What have you discovered that challenges this conventional wisdom? Example: \"The most successful salespeople focus on giving, not getting\" or \"Great leaders create more leaders\" SECTION C: AUDIENCE & MARKET C1. Target Audience (Required) Primary reader profile: C-Suite executives Middle managers Entrepreneurs/Small business owners Sales professionals General business audience Industry-specific: _______________ General fiction readers Genre-specific readers: _______________ C2. Audience Size (Required) Niche (under 100K potential readers) Focused (100K-1M potential readers) Broad (1M+ potential readers) Mass market (10M+ potential readers) C3. Competition Analysis (Required) Which successful books does your concept most closely relate to? List 2-3 titles and explain how yours is different/better C4. Reader Outcome (Required - Open text) After reading your book, what will readers be able to do differently? SECTION D: STORY STRUCTURE (Conditional based on fiction/nonfiction selection) For Fiction (D-Fiction): D-F1. Story Premise (Required - Open text) One-sentence story description: D-F2. Central Conflict (Required) What's the main obstacle your protagonist faces? External: Business/career challenge Internal: Personal growth/mindset shift Relationship: Team/family/partner dynamics Societal: Industry/cultural change Combination of above D-F3. Character Arc (Required - Open text) How does your protagonist change from beginning to end? D-F4. Supporting Characters (Required) Key supporting roles needed: Mentor figure Antagonist/challenger Ally/supporter Love interest Family member Business partner Other: _______________ For Nonfiction (D-Nonfiction): D-N1. Parable Protagonist (Required - Open text) Describe your main character (reader surrogate): Name, role, current situation, primary challenge D-N2. Mentor Character (Required - Open text) Describe your wise guide (author surrogate): Name, background, teaching style, unique insights D-N3. Core Principles (Required) How many main principles will you teach? 3 principles 5 principles 7 principles Other number: _______________ D-N4. Teaching Method (Required) How will wisdom be conveyed? Dialogue between mentor and protagonist Situations that demonstrate principles Other characters as examples Business scenarios and outcomes Combination approach SECTION E: UNIQUE ELEMENTS E1. Hook Factor (Required - Open text) Complete this sentence: \"You have to read this book because...\" E2. Shareability Test (Required - Open text) What will readers immediately want to tell their friends about your book? E3. Unique Positioning (Required) What makes your approach different? Completely new perspective Combination of existing ideas in new way Contrarian viewpoint Personal experience/story Research-based insights Industry insider knowledge E4. Visual Elements (Required) Will your book include: Diagrams/frameworks Infographics Character illustrations Process flowcharts Photos/images Text-only SECTION F: PLATFORM & GOALS F1. Current Platform (Required) Your existing audience size: No platform yet (starting fresh) Small (under 1,000 followers) Growing (1,000-10,000 followers) Established (10,000-100,000 followers) Large (100,000+ followers) F2. Primary Platform (Required) Where is your audience concentrated? LinkedIn Twitter/X Instagram YouTube Email list Speaking circuit Industry publications No platform yet F3. Success Metrics (Required) Primary definition of success: Book sales numbers Speaking opportunities Business growth Industry recognition Movement creation Creative satisfaction F4. Timeline (Required) Desired completion timeline: 1 day (outline and framework) 1 week (first draft) 1 month (polished manuscript) 3 months (complete book) 6+ months (extensive development) SECTION G: IMPLEMENTATION PREFERENCES G1. Writing Style (Required) Preferred approach: AI-assisted rapid creation AI-guided human writing Traditional self-writing with AI support Collaborative AI-human process G2. Content Depth (Required) Desired book length: Short parable (15,000-25,000 words) Standard business book (40,000-60,000 words) Comprehensive guide (60,000+ words) Novella length (25,000-40,000 words) G3. Additional Assets Needed (Required) Beyond the book, what do you want created? Marketing copy and hooks Cover design concepts Social media content Speaking presentation Course/workshop outline Website/landing page copy All of the above 🔄 Conditional Logic Flow for Google Sheets Logic Tree Structure: Copy IF A1 = \"Fiction Writer\" THEN → Show B-Fiction, D-Fiction sections AND → Focus on theme development, character arcs, emotional resonance AND → Generate fiction-specific outputs IF A1 = \"Nonfiction/Business Writer\" THEN → Show B-Nonfiction, D-Nonfiction sections AND → Focus on paradox development, principle teaching, authority building AND → Generate business parable outputs IF A1 = \"Hybrid\" THEN → Show both Fiction and Nonfiction sections AND → Blend approaches based on primary goal (A3) IF A3 = \"Bestseller success\" THEN → Emphasize hook development and shareability factors IF A3 = \"Thought leadership platform\" THEN → Focus on authority building and community creation IF F4 = \"1 day\" THEN → Generate rapid outline and framework only IF F4 = \"1 week\" THEN → Generate complete first draft with all supporting materials Google Sheets Implementation: Data Validation: Create dropdown menus for all multiple choice questions Conditional Formatting: Hide/show sections based on A1 selection Formula Logic: Use IF/THEN statements to populate agent prompts Output Generation: Trigger LLM calls based on completed sections Quality Control: Validation checks before content"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"[Content truncated — view full chat at source URL]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=e37bfd48-8673-4053-a7c1-7fd016b4fa22","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=e37bfd48-8673-4053-a7c1-7fd016b4fa22"}]}]}]
